cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on a novel representation for 3D objects designed for robots to estimate pose, class, and 3D geometry. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also utilizes deep learning methods (cs.LG, cs.AI) and linear subspace methods (cs.GR) to efficiently learn nonlinear object representations. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.RO and cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.GR.
